WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
AMNA NAWAZ: This week, a task force dedicated to&nbsp;
fighting antisemitism reportedly decided to sever&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:10.480
ties with the conservative Heritage Foundation.&nbsp;
It comes after the think tank's president,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:16.320
Kevin Roberts, defended Tucker Carlson's&nbsp;
interview with a far right antisemitic activist.

00:00:16.320 --> 00:00:18.320
This infighting has laid bare a growing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:22.960
schism within conservative circles&nbsp;
over how to address antisemitism.

00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:25.238
William Brangham reports.

00:00:25.238 --> 00:00:27.004
TUCKER CARLSON, Conservative Commentator:&nbsp;
Nick Fuentes, thank you for doing this.

00:00:27.004 --> 00:00:27.904
NICK FUENTES, Far Right Influencer:&nbsp;
Yes, thank you for having me.

00:00:27.904 --> 00:00:29.200
TUCKER CARLSON: I have wanted to meet you.

00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:34.240
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The interview, which lasted over&nbsp;
two hours, was posted late last month and has been&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:40.320
seen over 20 million times, the conservative&nbsp;
commentator Tucker Carlson interviewing Nick&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:47.360
Fuentes, the 27-year-old hard-right influencer&nbsp;
with millions of followers known as Groypers.

00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:49.840
Fuentes is known for his open racism.

00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:53.742
NICK FUENTES: White people have a&nbsp;
special heritage here as Americans.

00:00:53.742 --> 00:00:56.960
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: His misogyny,&nbsp;
like when he wrote, "Your body,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:56.960 --> 00:00:59.746
my choice," after the 2024 election.

00:00:59.746 --> 00:01:04.400
NICK FUENTES: The whole political&nbsp;
system is just based around women&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:07.902
never being accountable for any of their choices.

00:01:07.902 --> 00:01:10.080
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And his overt antisemitism,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:15.200
ranging from Holocaust denial to his&nbsp;
belief in a global Jewish conspiracy.

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:18.800
NICK FUENTES: The big challenge to&nbsp;
that is organized Jewry in America.

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:21.520
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The interview&nbsp;
with Carlson drew quick,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:21.520 --> 00:01:25.600
sharp condemnation from many&nbsp;
in the conservative movement.

00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:30.800
Ben Shapiro, editor of the conservative&nbsp;
Daily Wire, wrote: "No to the Groypers,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:35.313
no to the cowards like Tucker&nbsp;
Carlson who normalized their trash."

00:01:35.313 --> 00:01:36.480
KEVIN ROBERTS, President, Heritage&nbsp;
Foundation: Christians can critique&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:39.422
the state of Israel without being antisemitic.

00:01:39.422 --> 00:01:44.640
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But Kevin Roberts, head of The&nbsp;
Heritage Foundation, defended Carlson. Heritage&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:50.560
is the influential conservative think tank&nbsp;
behind Project 2025 and which has long supported&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:56.785
Israel and America's support for it. Roberts&nbsp;
argued attacking Carlson was a distraction.

00:01:56.785 --> 00:02:01.280
KEVIN ROBERTS: The venomous coalition attacking&nbsp;
him are sowing division. Their attempt to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:07.680
cancel him will fail. Most importantly, the&nbsp;
American people expect us to be focusing on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:12.000
our political adversaries on the left,&nbsp;
not attacking our friends on the right.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:17.600
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Roberts faced a strong backlash,&nbsp;
including from staffers within Heritage, and calls&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:23.440
for his resignation. He later apologized&nbsp;
and denounced Nick Fuentes specifically.

00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:26.000
But the controversy has revealed the ongoing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:30.560
challenge of balancing different&nbsp;
factions within the MAGA base.

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:33.428
For the "PBS News Hour," I'm William Brangham.

00:02:33.428 --> 00:02:37.200
AMNA NAWAZ: For more on this, we're joined by&nbsp;
Arno Rosenfeld. He's an enterprise reporter with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:37.200 --> 00:02:42.720
The Forward. That's a Jewish news outlet, where&nbsp;
he writes the Antisemitism Decoded newsletter.

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:43.630
Thanks for being here, Arno.

00:02:43.630 --> 00:02:44.628
ARNO ROSENFELD, Enterprise Reporter,&nbsp;
The Forward: Thanks for having me.

00:02:44.628 --> 00:02:48.320
AMNA NAWAZ: So, this interview, for&nbsp;
Tucker Carlson, who's a former FOX host&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.320 --> 00:02:52.720
and mainstay of conservative media,&nbsp;
to invite a known Holocaust denier,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:57.040
a white supremacist in Nick Fuentes onto&nbsp;
his show for an objectively friendly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:57.040 --> 00:03:00.144
interview, what does that moment&nbsp;
represent? Why would he do that?

00:03:00.144 --> 00:03:02.160
ARNO ROSENFELD: So, I think a&nbsp;
few things are going on here,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:05.920
because in addition to being all the things&nbsp;
that you described about Nick Fuentes,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:12.240
he's also an incredibly influential pundit in&nbsp;
a certain corner of the conservative movement.

00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:16.400
He has many -- hundreds of thousands of&nbsp;
people tune into his livestreams. He has&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:22.480
millions of followers online. And I think Carlson&nbsp;
recognized that Fuentes is growing in influence,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:27.600
and Carlson wanted to harness that influence. In&nbsp;
this case, he was really trying to get Fuentes to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:32.480
align with him on trying to get the MAGA&nbsp;
movement to withdraw support for Israel.

00:03:32.480 --> 00:03:35.920
And, as part of that, he was trying to&nbsp;
convince Fuentes to back away from some&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:41.680
of his more inflammatory rhetoric around Jews,&nbsp;
because Carlson thought that was bad for the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:44.880
larger goal that they shared of trying&nbsp;
to reduce American support for Israel.

00:03:44.880 --> 00:03:49.120
So that's why Carlson had Fuentes on. It&nbsp;
wasn't just about giving him a platform,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:49.120 --> 00:03:53.040
but it was about trying to sort of win&nbsp;
him over or build an alliance. And I think&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:57.440
that's what worried a lot of people, because&nbsp;
Carlson has a lot more mainstream credibility&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:57.440 --> 00:04:01.748
than Fuentes does. And so, if they're joining&nbsp;
forces, that's concerning to a lot of people.

00:04:01.748 --> 00:04:07.024
AMNA NAWAZ: Is that shift, is that illustrative&nbsp;
of a larger split or divide within conservatives?

00:04:07.024 --> 00:04:11.040
ARNO ROSENFELD: Absolutely. I mean, Trump has 
historically supported&nbsp;Israel. But there is a real dividing line

00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:13.440
there. And we're starting to see some&nbsp;
breakaways in Congress too, folks like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:18.160
Marjorie Taylor Greene becoming more hostile&nbsp;
to American aid for Israel, but, on the right,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:24.080
especially folks like Carlson, certainly people&nbsp;
like Fuentes, join that hostility toward support&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:28.468
for Israel with just overt antisemitism,&nbsp;
tropes, conspiracy theories about Jews.

00:04:28.468 --> 00:04:31.520
AMNA NAWAZ: So then you have the statement&nbsp;
from the president of The Heritage Foundation,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:35.504
right, stepping in to defend&nbsp;
Carlson. What do you make of that?

00:04:35.504 --> 00:04:39.200
ARNO ROSENFELD: So I think it was sort of, in&nbsp;
some respects, an unforced error on the part&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:39.200 --> 00:04:42.640
of The Heritage Foundation. Nobody was&nbsp;
actually asking them to weigh in here.

00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:46.800
And so the fact that Roberts would&nbsp;
go out of his way to defend Carlson,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:51.040
not just as a friend, but as a legitimate&nbsp;
voice in the conservative movement, and his&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:55.760
decision to interview Fuentes as a legitimate&nbsp;
political decision alarmed a lot of people,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:55.760 --> 00:05:00.080
because I think there are folks who recognize&nbsp;
that Fuentes might be growing in influence,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:02.480
but he's on these dark corners of the Internet.

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:06.960
And you can't really police those very&nbsp;
well. Carlson was booted from FOX News.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:06.960 --> 00:05:11.440
He's also independent right now. But&nbsp;
Heritage is still a very influential&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:11.440 --> 00:05:16.160
gatekeeper and policy voice within&nbsp;
the MAGA movement in Washington, D.C.

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:21.360
And so if it's not just Carlson as a more&nbsp;
mainstream voice than Fuentes bringing Fuentes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:26.400
along, but then it's Heritage giving their stamp&nbsp;
of approval to Carlson, I think that's what scared&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:30.160
a lot of people. They started thinking, oh, my&nbsp;
gosh, where are the gatekeepers? Who's going to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:35.760
stop this open antisemitism and animosity toward&nbsp;
Jews from entering the political mainstream?

00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:40.400
AMNA NAWAZ: Yes. So what about that? What about the 
keepers of&nbsp;that firewall, as it were? Because you have

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:45.760
seen people like Mitch McConnell and Ted Cruz&nbsp;
and Ben Shapiro come out against Nick Fuentes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:45.760 --> 00:05:51.200
unequivocally. But now you have him being hosted&nbsp;
on a show with Tucker Carlson. Is he existing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:55.520
in the dark corners or is that force and that&nbsp;
voice more ascendant among conservative circles?

00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:57.680
ARNO ROSENFELD: You know, I&nbsp;
think what Carlson realized,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:57.680 --> 00:06:01.600
and I think the reason that Carlson -- and he said&nbsp;
this in the conversation with Fuentes -- brought&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:05.840
Fuentes on is because those gatekeepers&nbsp;
have not been able to stop Fuentes' rise.

00:06:05.840 --> 00:06:09.040
One thing that Fuentes talked about&nbsp;
in that interview was his longstanding&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:09.040 --> 00:06:12.560
feud with Ben Shapiro, who he said for&nbsp;
years has been trying to keep him out&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:16.560
of the mainstream. And it hasn't&nbsp;
worked. So we did see -- I mean,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:21.280
the backlash was strong, and it does seem&nbsp;
like Roberts had to apologize. Heritage has&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:25.360
walked a little bit of this back. They have&nbsp;
certainly been receptive to the criticism.

00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:27.680
But the fact that it would even happen in the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:31.268
first place is a sign of how&nbsp;
much the discourse has moved.

00:06:31.268 --> 00:06:34.320
AMNA NAWAZ: I also want to point out President&nbsp;
Trump has met with Nick Fuentes before at&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:37.440
Mar-a-Lago. He said he didn't know who he&nbsp;
was or what he stood for. But he also met&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:42.560
with Kanye West, who has been antisemitic&nbsp;
and pro-Hitler in some of his remarks.

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:46.544
That was years ago, though. Is there&nbsp;
something different about this moment?

00:06:46.544 --> 00:06:51.520
ARNO ROSENFELD: I think that is a part&nbsp;
of how we got to this moment. So I think&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:55.040
this is the culmination of years of these trends.

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:58.640
I mean, Donald Trump, in 2016,&nbsp;
I think, really called the bluff&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:58.640 --> 00:07:02.560
of a lot of Republican politicians who'd&nbsp;
been hinting at various things, but hadn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:06.000
said them openly about immigrants,&nbsp;
for example. And Fuentes, I think,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:11.520
has called the bluff of conservative media,&nbsp;
who have hinted at globalists, for example.

00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:14.880
And Fuentes just comes out and says, no,&nbsp;
we're talking about Jews. And so I think&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:14.880 --> 00:07:18.960
that they're very like-minded in that sense&nbsp;
of saying, we don't have to talk around this&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:23.280
stuff. We don't have to use euphemisms.&nbsp;
We can just say it. And Trump came back&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:23.280 --> 00:07:28.708
to office. Fuentes got a bigger platform. So it's&nbsp;
really a culmination more than a shift, I think.

00:07:28.708 --> 00:07:31.200
AMNA NAWAZ: But what does all the&nbsp;
rhetoric mean in the real world? We&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:34.320
know there's a connection between what&nbsp;
is said when it comes to antisemitism&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:38.960
and real-world violence against Jews.&nbsp;
How are American Jews looking at this?

00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:42.720
ARNO ROSENFELD: I think what's really scary&nbsp;
for a lot of American Jews and one thing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:48.000
that American Jews have cared a lot about are&nbsp;
the maintenance of liberal democratic norms,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:53.440
not a partisan thing, so much as maintaining&nbsp;
gatekeepers of sort of polite society,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:59.040
maintaining the ability to say, this rhetoric&nbsp;
is beyond the pale. We can't tolerate this.

00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:02.800
And so, as those things break down,&nbsp;
it's less that there's a one-to-one,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:02.800 --> 00:08:06.480
somebody watches that interview and goes out&nbsp;
and commits an act of antisemitism. That may&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:11.520
happen here or there. It's more the sense&nbsp;
that, if you're a young person online a lot,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:11.520 --> 00:08:15.200
watching folks like Fuentes, you start&nbsp;
to think that this rhetoric is OK.

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:20.560
And so I think the idea that this is going to&nbsp;
become something that folks in Congress believe,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:25.588
that folks in the more mainstream media believe, I&nbsp;
think that's what's most alarming in this moment.

00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:29.184
AMNA NAWAZ: Arno Rosenfeld of The Forward,&nbsp;
thank you so much for joining us tonight.

00:08:29.184 --> 00:08:29.738
ARNO ROSENFELD: Thank you.

